<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>INTERNATIONAL&#174; VT 365 DIESEL ENGINE - POWER CYLINDERS - Installation - Connecting Rod/Piston Assembly
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="7">
        <title>Connecting Rod/Piston Assembly</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Turn crankshaft so number 1 crank pin is at bottom of its stroke.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2650725" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd04/d0410.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="312px"/>
            <caption>Figure 281. Piston and piston ring lubrication</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">
                <hotlnk xrefid="f2350716.1">Coat piston and piston rings with clean engine oil</hotlnk>.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2650726" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd06/d0613.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Figure 282. Cylinder wall lubrication</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">
                <hotlnk xrefid="f2350717">Coat cylinder walls, crankshaft journals, and piston cope with clean engine
                    oil</hotlnk>.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>To prevent engine damage,
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f2350718">CAM V8 stamped on top of the piston, must be oriented towards the camshaft
                        side of the crankcase
                    </hotlnk>
                    or up position.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <figure id="f2650727" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd06/d0624.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Figure 283. CAM V8 stamp on piston</caption>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Before installing piston and connecting rod assembly, make sure all piston cooling tubes are in
                    place.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <figure id="f2650728" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd04/d0415.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Figure 284. Piston installed in Piston Ring Compressor (Cope)</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place piston into Piston Ring Compressor .</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install bearing shells into connecting rod and cap. Coat bearing shell in connecting rod
                with clean engine oil.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Carefully place piston/piston cope combination and connecting rod assembly into crankcase
                bore.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>To prevent engine damage, use caution not to damage piston cooling tubes when installing
                    connecting rod / piston assemblies.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <figure id="f2650729" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd04/d0411a.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Figure 285. Installation of piston</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Once piston and connecting rod assembly have been inserted into cylinder bore, use the
                handle of a hammer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="f2350721">tap piston into crankcase bore</hotlnk>. Guide connecting rod into place on
                crankshaft.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Apply clean engine oil to connecting rod bolt hole threads and bearing shell in cap before
                installing bolts.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2650730" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd04/d0412.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Figure 286. Connecting rod and cap</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Matching numbers</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">
                <hotlnk xrefid="f2350722">Assemble cap to connecting rod with matching identification code</hotlnk>
                on same crankshaft journal from which it was removed. Make sure the longer leg of the connecting rod and
                the CAM V8 stamp on piston crown are oriented towards the camshaft.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>To prevent engine damage, do not use air powered tools when installing connecting rod bolts. This
                    may cause seizure of connecting rod bolts.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <figure id="f2650731" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd07/d0706.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Figure 287. Connecting rod cap</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Connecting rod bearing cap</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Connecting rod bolt</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <para></para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install and tighten connecting rod bolts evenly to the initial and final torque values. See
                Special Torques .
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Repeat installation procedure for remaining connecting rod and piston assemblies.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Check connecting rod side clearance with feeler gauge. See procedure in removal section .
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
